<h3 id="alignment"><a class="header-anchor" href="#alignment" aria-hidden="true">¶</a> Alignment</h3>
<p>Depending on your design, there are several different ways to align your label element.</p>
<demo-block class="demo-box" :jsfiddle="{&quot;html&quot;:&quot;&lt;el-radio-group v-model=\&quot;labelPosition\&quot; size=\&quot;small\&quot;&gt;\n  &lt;el-radio-button label=\&quot;left\&quot;&gt;Left&lt;/el-radio-button&gt;\n  &lt;el-radio-button label=\&quot;right\&quot;&gt;Right&lt;/el-radio-button&gt;\n  &lt;el-radio-button label=\&quot;top\&quot;&gt;Top&lt;/el-radio-button&gt;\n&lt;/el-radio-group&gt;\n&lt;div style=\&quot;margin: 20px;\&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;el-form :label-position=\&quot;labelPosition\&quot; label-width=\&quot;100px\&quot; :model=\&quot;formLabelAlign\&quot;&gt;\n  &lt;el-form-item label=\&quot;Name\&quot;&gt;\n    &lt;el-input v-model=\&quot;formLabelAlign.name\&quot;&gt;&lt;/el-input&gt;\n  &lt;/el-form-item&gt;\n  &lt;el-form-item label=\&quot;Activity zone\&quot;&gt;\n    &lt;el-input v-model=\&quot;formLabelAlign.region\&quot;&gt;&lt;/el-input&gt;\n  &lt;/el-form-item&gt;\n  &lt;el-form-item label=\&quot;Activity form\&quot;&gt;\n    &lt;el-input v-model=\&quot;formLabelAlign.type\&quot;&gt;&lt;/el-input&gt;\n  &lt;/el-form-item&gt;\n&lt;/el-form&gt;\n\n&quot;,&quot;script&quot;:&quot;\n  export default {\n    data() {\n      return {\n        labelPosition: 'right',\n        formLabelAlign: {\n          name: '',\n          region: '',\n          type: ''\n        }\n      };\n    }\n  }\n&quot;,&quot;style&quot;:null}">
                    <div class="source" slot="source"><el-radio-group v-model="labelPosition" size="small">
  <el-radio-button label="left">Left</el-radio-button>
  <el-radio-button label="right">Right</el-radio-button>
  <el-radio-button label="top">Top</el-radio-button>
</el-radio-group>
<div style="margin: 20px;"></div>
<el-form :label-position="labelPosition" label-width="100px" :model="formLabelAlign">
  <el-form-item label="Name">
    <el-input v-model="formLabelAlign.name"></el-input>
  </el-form-item>
  <el-form-item label="Activity zone">
    <el-input v-model="formLabelAlign.region"></el-input>
  </el-form-item>
  <el-form-item label="Activity form">
    <el-input v-model="formLabelAlign.type"></el-input>
  </el-form-item>
</el-form>

</div>
                    <p>The <code>label-position</code> attribute decides how labels align, it can be <code>top</code> or <code>left</code>. When set to <code>top</code>, labels will be placed at the top of the form field.</p>

